%%{init: {"theme": "neutral"} }%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Host
    participant Web as Web SPA<br/>(Wallet page)
    participant Sec as SecurityService
    participant HW as HostWalletService<br/>/ HostBookingsService
    participant DB as Postgres
    participant Mon as Monnify
    participant Wallet as WalletLedgerService

    note over Host,Wallet: Same shape for a payout (withdrawal) and a refund —<br/>only the target table (payouts vs refunds) and disburse call differ

    Host->>Web: request withdrawal (amount) / refund (booking)
    Web->>Sec: POST .../security/otp/challenge
    Sec-->>Host: OTP sent (email)
    Host->>Web: enter OTP + confirm

    Web->>HW: withdraw(amount, otpCode, idempotencyKey)<br/>/ refundBooking(bookingId, otpCode, idempotencyKey)

    rect rgb(245, 245, 245)
        note over HW,DB: insert-first idempotency claim
        HW->>DB: INSERT payouts/refunds row (status: processing)<br/>ON CONFLICT (hostId/bookingId, idempotencyKey) DO NOTHING
        alt row already existed with same amount
            DB-->>HW: cached row
            HW-->>Web: return cached result (idempotent replay)
        else same key, different amount
            DB-->>HW: conflicting row
            HW-->>Web: reject — stale key reuse
        end
    end

    HW->>Sec: verifyAndConsume(userId, "withdraw_funds"/"refund_booking", otpCode)
    alt OTP invalid/expired
        Sec-->>HW: failure
        HW->>DB: delete claim row
        HW-->>Web: error — retry with fresh OTP
    else OTP valid
        rect rgb(245, 245, 245)
            note over HW,Wallet: advisory-locked disburse (one transaction)
            HW->>DB: pg_advisory_xact_lock(hashtextextended(hostId, 2))
            HW->>DB: re-read balanceKobo under lock
            alt insufficient balance
                DB-->>HW: reject
            else sufficient balance
                HW->>Mon: disburse() (deterministic reference)<br/>or dedicated refund API if MONNIFY_USE_REFUND_API
                Mon-->>HW: disbursement reference + status
                HW->>DB: update payouts/refunds SET monnifyReference, status
                HW->>Wallet: appendEntry(debit, amountKobo,<br/>sourceType: payout|refund)
            end
        end
        HW-->>Web: success
    end

    opt refund only, MONNIFY_USE_REFUND_API on
        Mon->>HW: async refund webhook (SUCCESSFUL_REFUND / FAILED_REFUND)
        HW->>HW: RefundWebhookService.reconcile()
        note right of HW: on late failure, may emit a<br/>compensating credit ledger entry
    end

    note over HW: Known MVP gap - payouts have no webhook<br/>reconciliation. Any non-failed Monnify<br/>response is treated as final and debited immediately
